               <p>I am a <rs id="t17960406-55-viclabel310" type="occupation">publican</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17960406-55-victim577 t17960406-55-viclabel310"></join> in <placeName id="t17960406-55-crimeloc311">St. Ann's, Soho</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17960406-55-crimeloc311" type="placeName" value="St. Ann's, Soho"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17960406-55-crimeloc311" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17960406-55-off308 t17960406-55-crimeloc311"></join>; the prisoner came to my house on the 21st of March, and called for a pennyworth of porter; she sat down some little time and drank it; after she had sat some time, she took an opportunity of going out to the back part of my house, where I usually put my pots; she came back and drank the remainder of her porter, and then went out; I did not miss the property immediately, but in the afternoon I missed two new pewter pint pots.</p>
               <p>JOHN ISLIP sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a constable of Vintry-ward: On the 21st of March, Mrs. Twitchell sent for me; I saw the prisoner in the passage behind the bar, at Mrs. Twitchwell's, the King's-head; I searched her and found one pot upon her, and three others she had in her hand, and one was fastened behind her, under her cloaths, (producing it).</p>
               <p>Merritt. This is one of the pots that I lost.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17960406-55-verdict312" type="verdictDescription">
